	<h2>Privacy Fence Height Strategies</h2>

	<h3>Standard 6-Foot Privacy Fence</h3>
	<p>Most common height for backyard privacy in Stockton:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Effectiveness:</strong> Blocks sight lines from ground level and standard seating</li>
		<li><strong>Regulations:</strong> Maximum height in most Stockton backyards without permits</li>
		<li><strong>Cost advantage:</strong> Least expensive height, standard materials readily available</li>
		<li><strong>Limitations:</strong> Doesn't block views from second-story windows or elevated decks</li>
		<li><strong>Ideal situations:</strong> Single-story homes, flat yards, neighbors at same elevation</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Enhanced 8-Foot Privacy Fence</h3>
	<p>Superior privacy solution for challenging situations:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Effectiveness:</strong> Blocks most two-story window views, excellent ground privacy</li>
		<li><strong>Regulations:</strong> Requires permit in Stockton, HOA approval often needed</li>
		<li><strong>Cost increase:</strong> 35-50% more than 6-foot fence due to materials and engineering</li>
