	<h2>Privacy Fence Maintenance for Longevity</h2>

	<h3>Wood Fence Maintenance Schedule</h3>
	<p>Preserve privacy and appearance with proper care:</p>

	<p><strong>Annual Tasks:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Inspect for loose boards, nails, and structural issues</li>
		<li>Clean fence with mild soap and water or pressure washer (low pressure)</li>
		<li>Check for and treat any signs of rot or insect damage</li>
		<li>Trim vegetation away from fence to prevent moisture damage</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Every 2-3 Years:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Re-stain or re-seal fence to maintain water resistance</li>
		<li>Replace any damaged or severely warped boards</li>
		<li>Tighten or replace loose hardware</li>
		<li>Apply fresh coat of paint if fence is painted</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Every 5-7 Years:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>Strip and refinish fence if previous finish is failing</li>
		<li>Replace sections with significant rot or damage</li>
		<li>Re-evaluate post stability, reinforce if needed</li>
	</ul>

